## ğŸ“ How to Add to YOUR Project

### Method 1: Copy the Component Folder

1. **Copy** the `src/components/BeamGrid/` folder
2. **Paste** it into your project's `components/` folder
3. **Use it** in any page:

```jsx
import BeamGridBackground from "@/components/BeamGrid/BeamGridBackground";

export default function MyPage() {
  return (
    <div className="relative h-screen bg-black">
      {/* The animated background */}
      <BeamGridBackground />
      
      {/* Your content on top */}
      <div className="relative z-10 flex h-full items-center justify-center">
        <h1 className="text-6xl font-bold text-white">
          Your Heading Here
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

## ğŸ¨ Change Colors

Want different colors? Just add these props:

### Cyan (Default)
```jsx
<BeamGridBackground />
```

### Purple
```jsx
<BeamGridBackground
  beamColor="rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.6)"
  darkBeamColor="rgba(217, 70, 239, 0.8)"
/>
```

### Green
```jsx
<BeamGridBackground
  beamColor="rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.7)"
  darkBeamColor="rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.9)"
/>
```

### Pink
```jsx
<BeamGridBackground
  beamColor="rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.6)"
  darkBeamColor="rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.9)"
/>
```

